textDelta: Making positive changes towards the advancment of civilization is progress played to music.
For progress to happen, one must take the lead.
Sometimes you have to spin around and around before progress can happen.
Progress is much more than a mosh pit.

textDelta: To keep up with progress, one cannot be a step or two behind.
Learn and practice the steps, and progress will follow.
When progress is your goal, play lively music and move to the beat.
Sometimes, to get progress moving, one must get out there on the floor and start shaking their hips to the music.
When trying to progress, watch out for those who will step on your toes.
If you want to progess, you have to move your feet.
